    <p><inlineCode parentName="p">{`Highlight`}</inlineCode>{` and `}<inlineCode parentName="p">{`Snippet`}</inlineCode>{` imported from `}<inlineCode parentName="p">{`react-instantsearch-dom`}</inlineCode>{` both display attributes of matching search results to the user. Their distinction is that the former renders it in full (e.g. a title, date or list of tags) whereas the latter only shows a snippet, i.e. a text passage of given length surrounding the matching string (e.g. for body texts). In each case the `}<inlineCode parentName="p">{`attribute`}</inlineCode>{` prop should be the name of the property as it was assigned in `}<inlineCode parentName="p">{`src/utils/algolia.js`}</inlineCode>{` and as it appears in your Algolia indices.`}</p>
